d 'XTCOMBREAK': module to estimate the common break date with a confidence interval (Bai 2010) and test whether the break really is common across units (Jiang and Kurozumi 2026)
d
d	xtcombreak implements two complementary papers on common
d breaks in panel data.    xtcombreak estimate implements Bai
d (2010). In a single time series only the break fraction can be
d estimated consistently; the	 break date cannot. Bai's result is
d that a panel fixes this: as N grows, P(khat = k0) -> 1, so the
d exact date is recovered. This    holds even when a regime
d contains a {bf:single observation}, which makes it useful for
d pinning down the onset of a new regime    quickly. The command
d estimates the date by least squares, quasi-maximum likelihood or
d feasible GLS, reports Bai's parameter-free	confidence
d interval, and runs his series-by-series Chow test to say which
d units actually broke.    xtcombreak test implements Jiang and
d Kurozumi (2026). Every common-break method, including Bai's,
d assumes the break is at the	 same date for all units. This is a
d real restriction and can fail. The command tests that assumption
d with a self-normalised CUSUM	  statistic built from OLS
d residuals. 
d
d KW: panel data
d KW: structural breaks
d KW: common breaks
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260717
d
d Author:   Merwan Roudane, NA
d Support: email  merwanroudane920@@gmail.com
d
f xtcombreak.ado
f xtcombreak.sthlp
f xtcombreak_methods.sthlp
f xtcombreak_estimate.sthlp
f xtcombreak_test.sthlp
f xtcombreak_example.do
